ator access, and the apartment door while the actual key is for the mailbox</u>.</b>&nbsp;Your mailbox number is different from the apartment number for security reasons.</span></li><li style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif; font-size:11pt; color:black; margin:0in"><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14pt">You can park on any level, enter the building through the black door (see photo above) then take the elevator to your floor.</span><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14pt; background-color:lime">&nbsp;Please be aware that there is not an exterior elevator that is accessible from the parking garage. On each parking level&nbsp;there are single doors located in the left and right corners that require your gray fob to gain entry into the building.&nbsp;You must hold your gray fob against the red sensor on the black box which is next to the door. Wait for the light to turn green and pull on the handle for entrance (see photo above).</span></li><li style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif; font-size:11pt; color:black; margin:0in"><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14pt; background-color:lime">Upon entering the building, there is no signage that directs you to the elevators.&nbsp;You will need to take a right and the elevators will be on your left. Once in the elevator you must place your gray fob against the red sensor on the lower right corner of the elevator panel, then select your floor.</span><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14pt">&nbsp;</span></li><li style="font-family:Aptos,sans-serif; font-size:11pt; color:black; margin:0in"><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14pt">Twice Blessed House has a bell cart for your use during business hours only </span><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14pt; background-color:yellow"><b>Monday ‚Äì Friday 8:00 - 4:30</b></span><span style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Aptos,sans-seri